# üö´ No Hardcoding Rule

## Purpose
Ensure all components are built from tokens, not raw values, to maintain consistency with the design system.

---

## Rule

1. **Never hardcode raw values** (hex codes, px, rem, font names).  
   - ‚ùå Wrong: `color: #0C0C0C;`  
   - ‚ùå Wrong: `padding: 16px;`  
   - ‚ùå Wrong: `border-radius: 8px;`  

2. **Always use semantic tokens** exported from Figma.  
   - ‚úÖ Correct: `color: var(--text-neutral-body);`  
   - ‚úÖ Correct: `padding: var(--spacing-md);`  
   - ‚úÖ Correct: `border-radius: var(--radius-md);`  

3. **Responsive values** must also come from tokens (`responsive.json`).  
   - ‚úÖ Correct: `font-size: var(--font-size-title-xs-mobile);`  

4. **Components** must be composed entirely of tokens.  
   - Example (Button):  
     ```css
     .button-primary {
       background: var(--surface-primary-default);
       color: var(--text-inverse);
       padding: var(--spacing-sm) var(--spacing-md);
       border-radius: var(--radius-md);
       font-size: var(--font-size-body-md);
     }
     .button-primary:hover {
       background: var(--surface-primary-hover);
     }
     .button-primary:disabled {
       background: var(--surface-neutral-disabled);
       color: var(--text-neutral-disabled);
     }
     ```

---

## Summary
All values must resolve to **design tokens** defined in `mapped.json`, `components.json`, or `responsive.json`.  
No raw values are permitted in component CSS or JS.
